sku.name: Day of the Dead Scotch Bonnet Hot Sauce
sku.longDescription: Often mistaken for the Habanero, the Scotch Bonnet has a deeply inverted tip as opposed to the pointed end of the Habanero. Ranging in many colors from green to yellow-orange, the Scotch Bonnet is a staple in West Indies and Barbados style pepper sauces.

org.broadleafcommerce.core.order.domain..name: Cafe Louisiane Sweet Cajun Blackening Sauce

sku.name: Cafe Louisiane Sweet Cajun Blackening Sauce
sku.longDescription: One of the more unusual sauces we sell. The original was an old style Cajun sauce and this is it's updated blackening version. It's sweet but you get a great hit of cinnamon and cloves with a nice kick of cayenne heat. Use on all foods to give that Cajun flair!
